Third-party components
----------------------

This product integrates the following third-party components. Each component
remains under its own license; their licenses are fully compatible with
Apache 2.0 redistribution. None of these components are modified; we use them
as libraries via published package interfaces.

Trystero
    https://github.com/dmotz/trystero
    License: MIT
    Used for: peer discovery via public WebTorrent trackers.
    Loaded at runtime from jsDelivr CDN; not vendored.

Python-SimConnect
    https://github.com/odwdinc/Python-SimConnect
    License: MIT-compatible (see upstream repository)
    Used for: reading live aircraft / avatar state from MSFS via Microsoft's
    public SimConnect interface.

websockets (Python library)
    https://github.com/python-websockets/websockets
    License: BSD-3-Clause
    Used for: HTTP + WebSocket server within the Python process.

pygame
    https://github.com/pygame/pygame
    License: LGPL-2.1
    Used for: USB joystick / HOTAS / button-box polling.
    Note: pygame is used as a dynamically-linked library only (via official
    pip wheels); we do not modify pygame's source or statically link against
    it, which satisfies the LGPL's requirements for use in non-LGPL programs.

PyInstaller
    https://github.com/pyinstaller/pyinstaller
    License: GPL-2.0 with bootloader exception
    Used at build time only to produce distributable Windows executables.
    The PyInstaller bootloader exception explicitly permits distributing the
    bundled application under a non-GPL license (Apache 2.0 in our case).

WiX Toolset (v6)
    https://github.com/wixtoolset/wix
    License: MS-RL (Microsoft Reciprocal License) — open source
    Used for: building the MSI installer.

Tailwind CSS (browser build)
    https://tailwindcss.com
    License: MIT
    Loaded at runtime from jsDelivr CDN; not vendored.

Public WebTorrent trackers (network service, not code)
    Operators: openwebtorrent.com and similar community trackers.
    Usage: tracker protocol only, for peer matchmaking via wss://.
    No audio data transits these trackers — only short SDP signaling
    exchanges that establish direct WebRTC connections between peers.

Audio assets
------------

Ambient sound samples bundled in `web/assets/`. Each sample is used under
its individual license as documented below. Samples are trimmed and
seamlessly looped at runtime via runtime crossfade; the original files
are not redistributed as standalone products.

    web/assets/footstep.mp3
        Source: Freesound — sound id 851919 by user "Gasdust_cloud"
                ("asphalt sneakers steps")
        URL:    https://freesound.org/s/851919/
        License: Creative Commons 0 (CC0) — public domain dedication.
        Used as: walker ambient (footstep loop) for any peer in walker
                mode while the peer is moving.

    web/assets/propeller.mp3
        Source: Freesound — sound id 737571 by user "therandomsoundbyte2637"
                ("N386EP 2022 Textron Aviation Inc 172S")
        URL:    https://freesound.org/s/737571/
        License: Creative Commons 0 (CC0) — public domain dedication.
        Used as: cockpit ambient for piston / turboprop aircraft
                (selected when MSFS SimVar ENGINE TYPE is 0 or 5).

    web/assets/jet.mp3
        Source: Freesound — sound id 100432 by user "2hear"
                ("Transatlantic jet internal cruising")
        URL:    https://freesound.org/s/100432/
        License: Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International (CC-BY 4.0).
                https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/
        Attribution: Original sound by "2hear" (Freesound). Used unmodified
                in form (only trimmed and looped for playback). Redistributed
                as part of VoiceWalker under CC-BY 4.0; the present NOTICE
                file constitutes the required attribution.
        Used as: cockpit ambient for jet aircraft
                (selected when MSFS SimVar ENGINE TYPE is 1).

    web/assets/helicopter.mp3
        Source: Freesound — sound id 436449 by user "underlineddesigns"
                ("helicopter rotor")
        URL:    https://freesound.org/s/436449/
        License: Creative Commons 0 (CC0) — public domain dedication.
        Used as: cockpit ambient for helicopters
                (selected when MSFS SimVar ENGINE TYPE is 3).

Google Public STUN
    stun.l.google.com:19302 (and equivalents).
    Usage: Session Traversal Utilities for NAT — a free public service
    operated by Google, designed for exactly this kind of WebRTC usage.
    No code from Google is linked into this product; we only send STUN
    binding requests to discover our public-side network address.

